  {
    "author": "Darl Anthony Pepito",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "version": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Resolution - SM-864: Vendor Admin - Add AG Grid Filters and Sorting\n\nMR: https://gitlab.com/powerslice-software-development/sm-spa/-/merge_requests/18\nBranch: SM-864\n\nChanges:\n- Added multi-column sort support (Ctrl+click) for sorting by multiple columns\n- Added static visible column menu with Filter, General, and Columns tabs\n- Added Apply and Reset buttons to all filter dropdowns\n- Changed default text filter from equals to contains\n- Added auto-populated distinct values for all Set filter dropdowns via API\n- Added filter and sort state persistence via localStorage\n- Added Clear All Filters button in toolbar\n- Fixed floating filter row CSS overlap issue\n\nQA Testing Steps:\n1. Navigate to Vendor Admin grid\n2. Click any column header (e.g. Company Name) - verify it sorts A-Z, then Z-A on second click\n3. Hold Ctrl and click a second column header - verify multi-column sort works with numbered indicators\n4. Open a filter dropdown on any column - verify it shows Apply and Reset buttons\n5. Type in a text filter (e.g. Company Name) - verify it defaults to contains search\n6. Open a Set filter (e.g. Status, State) - verify distinct values are populated from the database\n7. Apply a filter and sort, then refresh the page (F5) - verify filter and sort persist\n8. Click Clear All Filters button - verify all filters and sort reset\n9. Hover over any column header - verify the hamburger menu icon is always visible\n10. Click the column menu - verify it shows Filter, General, and Columns tabs\n\nVersion: MR !18"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "created": "2026-02-10T11:21:19.511-0500"
  },
