          "type": "codeBlock",
          "attrs": {
            "language": "diff",
            "localId": "8a09062fd3b7"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Results on STAGE\n\nScenario 1 \u2013 Navigate to Vendor Admin Grid\n+ User can log in and reach the dashboard\n+ Vendor Admin AG Grid loads with vendor data via sidebar navigation\n+ Grid renders all columns with data, no CSS overlap on floating filter row, and no console errors\n\nScenario 2 \u2013 Single Column Sort Ascending\n+ Clicking Company Name header once sorts rows A-Z\n+ Ascending sort indicator arrow appears on column header\n+ All visible vendor names follow alphabetical A-Z order when scrolling\n\nScenario 3 \u2013 Single Column Sort Descending\n+ Clicking Company Name header a second time sorts rows Z-A\n+ Sort indicator changes to descending direction\n+ All visible vendor names follow reverse alphabetical Z-A order\n\nScenario 4 \u2013 Single Column Sort Clear\n+ Clicking Company Name header a third time removes the sort and returns to default order\n+ Sort indicator is no longer visible on the column header\n\n+ Scenario 5 \u2013 Multi-Column Sort\n+ Clicking State header sorts grid by State ascending\n+ Ctrl+clicking Company Name header adds a secondary sort within each State grouping\n+ Numbered sort indicators appear on both columns (State = 1, Company Name = 2)\n+ Company Names are in ascending order within each identical State value\n\nScenario 6 \u2013 Filter Dropdown Apply and Reset Buttons\n+ Filter dropdown opens on Company Name column with input field\n+ Apply and Reset buttons are visible at the bottom of the filter panel\n+ Typing a partial name without clicking Apply does not filter the grid\n+ Clicking Apply filters the grid to matching vendors only\n+ Clicking Reset clears the filter and restores the full dataset\n\nScenario 7 \u2013 Text Filter Defaults to Contains\n+ Default filter condition on Company Name is set to Contains, not Equals\n+ Typing a partial name (e.g. \"tech\") and clicking Apply returns all vendors whose Company Name contains the substring\n\nScenario 8 \u2013 Set Filter Distinct Values from Database\n+ Opening a Set-type column filter (e.g. Status or State) displays a checkbox list of distinct values\n+ Values are auto-populated from the database and not hardcoded\n+ Selecting one value and clicking Apply filters the grid to matching rows only\n+ Row count updates to reflect the filtered subset\n\n- Scenario 9 \u2013 Combining Multiple Filters with AND Logic\n- Filtering Status to Active shows only active vendors\n- Adding a second filter on State (e.g. California) further reduces the results\n- Combined row count is less than or equal to the Active-only count\n- Every displayed row matches both Status = Active AND State = California\n\nScenario 10 \u2013 Filter and Sort Persistence After Page Refresh\n+ Applying a State filter and Company Name sort, then refreshing the page with F5\n+ State filter is still active after reload\n+ Company Name ascending sort is still applied after reload\n\nScenario 11 \u2013 Clear All Filters Button\n+ Applying filters on two columns and a sort on one column\n+ Clicking Clear All Filters removes all filters and resets the sort\n+ Grid returns to the full dataset in default order\n+ No filter icons or highlights remain on any column headers\n\nScenario 12 \u2013 Column Menu Static Hamburger Icon\n+ Hamburger menu icon is always visible on column headers, not only on hover\n+ Icon is consistently present across at least three different columns\n\nScenario 13 \u2013 Column Menu Filter General and Columns Tabs\n+ Clicking the hamburger menu opens a column menu panel\n+ Menu contains a Filter tab with filter options\n+ Menu contains a General tab with column options (e.g. pin, autosize)\n+ Menu contains a Columns tab with visibility toggles for all columns\n+ All three tabs are present consistently across multiple columns\n\nScenario 14 \u2013 Column Rearranging via Drag and Drop\n+ Dragging a column header (e.g. State) to a new position shows a visual indicator\n+ Column repositions correctly on drop\n+ Data integrity is maintained with no row data misalignment after rearranging\n\nScenario 15 \u2013 Column Pinning\n+ Pinning Company Name to the left via the column menu General tab\n+ Pinned column stays fixed while scrolling horizontally\n+ Unpinning the column returns it to its normal scrollable position\n\nScenario 16 \u2013 Filter on Every Column\n+ Every column in the grid has a filter dropdown available\n+ Text columns show a text filter defaulting to Contains and set columns show a checkbox list\n+ Apply and Reset buttons are present on every column filter panel\n+ At least one filter per column type correctly reduces the dataset\n\nScenario 17 \u2013 Sort on Every Column\n+ Each column sorts ascending on first click and descending on second click\n+ Sort indicator arrows reflect the correct direction for each column\n\nScenario 18 \u2013 Filter with No Results\n+ Typing a non-matching string and clicking Apply shows zero rows with an empty state message\n+ Clicking Reset or Clear All Filters restores the full dataset\n\nScenario 19 \u2013 Special Characters in Filter\n+ Entering special characters (& ' \" < >) in the text filter does not cause JavaScript errors or broken UI\n+ Grid shows matching results or an empty state with no XSS or injection issues\n\nScenario 20 \u2013 Persistence Across Browser Sessions\n+ Applying a filter and sort, closing the browser tab, then reopening Vendor Admin restores the saved state from localStorage\n\nScenario 21 \u2013 Persistence Cleared by Clear All Filters\n+ Filter and sort persist after a page refresh\n+ Clicking Clear All Filters and then refreshing the page loads the grid with no filters or sorts applied\n\nScenario 22 \u2013 Multi-Column Sort with Three or More Columns\n+ Sorting by State, then Ctrl+clicking Status, then Ctrl+clicking Company Name\n+ Numbered indicators show 1, 2, and 3 on the respective columns\n+ Data is ordered correctly across all three sort levels\n\nScenario 23 \u2013 Filter Combined with Sort Respects Filtered Data\n+ Filtering State to Texas and sorting Company Name ascending shows only Texas vendors in A-Z order\n+ No non-Texas vendors appear in the sorted results\n\nScenario 24 \u2013 Large Dataset Performance\n+ Sorting the full unfiltered dataset completes without noticeable lag or UI freeze\n+ Applying a broad text filter (e.g. single letter \"a\") renders without significant delay\n\nScenario 25 \u2013 Column Visibility Toggle via Columns Tab\n+ Columns tab shows all available columns with checkboxes\n+ Unchecking a column hides it from the grid\n+ Re-checking the column makes it reappear with no data misalignment\n\nScenario 26 \u2013 Floating Filter Row No CSS Overlap\n+ Floating filter row is properly aligned with no overlap on header text or data rows\n+ Resizing the browser window does not cause the floating filter row to overlap\n\nScenario 27 \u2013 Regression: Core Grid Functionality\n+ Vendor data loads correctly without any filters applied\n+ Clicking a company name navigates to the Vendor Profile (SM-934)\n+ Grid export reflects the filtered dataset when filters are applied (SM-865)\n+ Add New Vendor button opens the new vendor form (SM-935)\n+ Inline editing functions correctly on editable cells (SM-863)\n+ No console errors on page load or during interactions"
            }
          ]
        },
